{"word":"G4594 - σήμερον - sḗmeron - say'-mer-on - This day","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">σήμερον</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong>sḗmeron"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong>say'-mer-on"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong>This day"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"இன்று, இன்றைய தினம், இன்னாள் - வினை யடை"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"today, this day"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>Part(s) of speech:</strong> Adverb / வினையடை</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English:</strong> Neuter (as adverb) of a presumed compound of the article <a href=\"#/G3588 - ὁ - ho - ho/3588\">G3588</a> (&ldquo;tau&rdquo; changed to &ldquo;sigma&rdquo;) and <a href=\"#/G2250 - ἡμέρα - hēméra - hay-mer'-ah/2250\">G2250</a>; on <i>the</i> (that is, <i>this</i>) <i>day</i> (or <i>night</i> current or just passed); genitively <i>now</i> (that is, at <i>present</i>, <i>hitherto</i>): - this (to-) day."},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"}]}